The paper deals with cognitive radio systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The optimization problem formulation and solution techniques used in the paper are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also mentions numerical simulations, which could fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed solutions, which could be considered as a machine learning or optimization problem and thus could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
